      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8;">

        <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
          Remodeling a kitchen, bathroom, basement, or entire home in Vernal? You need somewhere safe to put your furniture, appliances, and personal belongings while the work happens. Leaving everything crammed into one room risks damage from dust, paint overspray, and contractor foot traffic.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">Why Fort Knox Is Perfect for Renovation Storage</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>Dust-proof.</strong> Steel shipping containers are completely sealed. No construction dust, no drywall particles, no paint fumes reaching your belongings. When your renovation is done, everything comes back clean.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>Mouse-proof.</strong> Renovations can take weeks or months. In a standard wood-frame storage unit, mice will find your upholstered furniture and make nests in it. At Fort Knox, that's physically impossible — zero rodent entry points.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>Same-day move-in.</strong> Call James and you can have your unit ready the same day. No week-long wait, no application processing. This matters when your contractor says "we start demolition Monday."</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>Month-to-month flexibility.</strong> Renovations are unpredictable. If your project runs two months longer than planned, you're not locked into a long contract. Rent month-to-month for exactly as long as you need.</p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">What Fits?</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">A 20ft container holds the contents of a full apartment — couches, beds, dressers, boxes, kitchen items. If you're renovating your entire home and need to clear out everything including the garage, a 40ft container handles a full household easily.</p>

        
